@Nofish: probable a big bug:
helper.getFreeSpace() will return -1 if GetFreeSpace error:
- in Win, @nekocross reported win32file error, install crapi might help;
- in Android,  `    if "statvfs" in dir(os):  # Unix`  is not applied in Android

see: https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet/blob/master/src/util/helper.py#L53

So we need a nice fallback if GetFreeSpace error, otherwise, zeronet will delete  _ALL_ optional files due to  helper.getFreeSpace() return -1, see: https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet/blob/master/plugins/OptionalManager/ContentDbPlugin.py#L352

